    <!-- Help -->
    <string name="help_title">Help</string>
    <string name="help_conn_title">Connecting the keyboard</string>
    <string name="help_conn_usb">USB: plug the keyboard into the phone via a USB OTG adapter, then tap Connect.</string>
    <string name="help_conn_ble">Bluetooth: enable Bluetooth MIDI on the keyboard, tap Scan BLE, pick GO:KEYS / GO:PIANO.</string>
    <string name="help_layer_title">Layering &amp; split</string>
    <string name="help_layer_explain">The app turns on the keyboard\'s Performance Part Switch via Roland DT1 SysEx and routes each part to its own MIDI channel. This is the fix for the previous version where layering on channel 2 had no audible effect.</string>
    <string name="help_loopmix_title">LoopMix</string>
    <string name="help_loopmix_explain">Style and key are sent as NRPN on channel 1; Start/Stop is a Roland DT1 message at the LoopMix base address.</string>
    <string name="help_macro_title">Macros</string>
    <string name="help_macro_explain">Tap Record, perform any actions in the app, tap Stop. The recorded sequence is replayed with the same relative timing.</string>
    <string name="help_automation_title">Automations</string>
    <string name="help_automation_explain">Each rule has a trigger (incoming note / CC / SysEx prefix / patch select) and an action (panic, send raw bytes, switch a patch, toggle LoopMix, play a macro).</string>
    <string name="help_trouble_title">Troubleshooting</string>
    <string name="help_trouble_explain">If notes hang, hit PANIC. If the keyboard does not respond to layering, make sure the keyboard\'s DUAL/SPLIT button is off — the app drives layering itself via Performance Parts.</string>
